																		Author&#039;s Post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005044&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610181256" alt="Decibelles" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005044)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;" >Decibelles</a></span> <span class="odate time_1451703214 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Jan 2016 02:53</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2433074">
									

<p>Thanks to everyone who helped me out with this the past few months, to staff for supporting me, and to the community and fandom at large for making both this site wonderful, and for being relatively stable and peaceful and producing wonderful content. This is quite the project, and I'm still ironing out the final wrinkles with how to update it monthly.</p>
<p>Special huge thanks to the Russian site for doing this in the first place, and having it be such a cool concept that I was inspired to want to do it as well, and find a way to make it my own. You can find their version <a href="http://scpfoundation.ru/news">here</a>.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;How&nbsp;I&nbsp;pick&nbsp;what&nbsp;articles&nbsp;appear&nbsp;on&nbsp;here.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;How&nbsp;I&nbsp;pick&nbsp;what&nbsp;articles&nbsp;appear&nbsp;on&nbsp;here.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The only firm criteria is that an article must not be in the negatives at all. Beyond that, whoever is writing the new installment will pick based on discretion. One example: if an article appears to be rapidly sinking for various reasons by the time a new installment is written (and we've had cases of this happening before), then it will not be shown. If an article seems to be dipping in and out of the negatives, it may not be shown as well.</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;How&nbsp;I&nbsp;pick&nbsp;what&nbsp;articles&nbsp;appear&nbsp;on&nbsp;here.</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<p>This is honestly my favorite thing to work on for the site. I hope to continue it every month (or at least entrust it in the care of Community Outreach if emergencies come up :P).</p>
<p>Love you all! ❤</p>

							</div>

								
