															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005044&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610181256" alt="Decibelles" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005044)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;" >Decibelles</a></span> <span class="odate time_1478558975 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Nov 2016 22:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2687035">
									

<p>Just to clarify how I find art to post, I use five sources, in the following order of how much content I'm able to get from them:</p>
<ul>
<li>pixiv</li>
<li>tumblr</li>
<li>deviantArt</li>
<li>Twitter</li>
<li>Reddit</li>
</ul>
<p>There's not many restrictions, though I have a few:</p>
<ol>
<li>Art can't be NSFW. Light gore/violence is fine. Stylized gore/heavy violence is allowed if part of a pixiv photoset and not the cover image of said photoset).</li>
<li>The artist doesn't have NSFW art mixed with their SFW art. I'm fine with them having separate NSFW art on another blog/account, but if they have it mixed with their main art, no-go.</li>
<li>In the case of pixiv, I don't include an artist if they have NSFW art in the first page of their bookmarks (because I don't have the time to search through every single artist's bookmark pages).</li>
</ol>
<p>This is just to ensure I don't link anything of this nature to the under-18 crowd who uses this site and also not link to content that breaks Wikidot's Terms of Services. Better safe than sorry.</p>

							</div>

								
